13 Amend the amendment by inserting after Part X the following:
14 'PART Y
15 Sec. Y-1. Forensic audit requirement. All funds carried over from fiscal year
16 2024-25 to the 2026-2027 biennium in this Act, referred to in this Part as "the funds," are
17 subject to an independent forensic audit. The State Auditor, or a similarly qualified auditor
18 chosen by the State Auditor, referred to in this Part as "the auditor," shall conduct the audit
19 in compliance with this Part.
20 Sec. Y-2. Review and verification of use of funds to meet intent. The auditor,
21 in conducting the forensic audit, shall specifically review the use of the funds to verify that
22 these amounts are being used in accordance with their intended purpose as determined by
23 the Legislature. The auditor shall document the original intent behind the funds and confirm
24 that current allocations adhere to that intent.
25 Sec. Y-3. Report; legislation. The State Auditor shall submit the completed
26 forensic audit report, including findings regarding intent and adherence to that intent, to the
27 Joint Standing Committee on Appropriations and Financial Affairs by December 3, 2025
28 and make the report publicly available no later than 2 days after the conclusion of the audit.
29 The joint standing committee shall submit a bill to the Second Regular Session of the 132nd
30 Legislature addressing and correcting any discrepancies or misallocations identified in the
31 report.
32 Sec. Y-4. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
33 allocations are made.
34 AUDITOR, OFFICE OF THE STATE
35 Audit Bureau 0067
36 Initiative: Provides one-time funding to contract for an independent forensic audit.
